WEBVTT

00:33.858 --> 00:46.956
Welcome back to our study of Proverbs, and we are in Proverbs chapter 7, and we are going to actually focus now on verses 19 through 21.

00:48.078 --> 00:53.165
And let me read that text, and then we're going to go back and review a bit.

00:54.026 --> 01:02.578
So in chapter 7 of Proverbs verses 19 through 21, the Bible says, for my husband is not at home,

01:02.850 --> 01:04.552
He has gone on a long journey.

01:05.754 --> 01:07.716
He has taken a bag of money with him.

01:08.217 --> 01:10.880
At the full moon, he will come home.

01:11.801 --> 01:16.126
With her many persuasions, she entices him with her flattering lips.

01:16.787 --> 01:17.948
She seduces him.

01:18.609 --> 01:32.466
Now here we're talking about, well, the book Proverbs is talking about the wayward woman, but we have used her as an example of the world and the way that the world tries to disrupt the Christian's life.

01:32.610 --> 01:35.333
Now, what do I mean by world?

01:35.773 --> 01:52.492
I want you to hold your place for just a moment and I want you to go to Ephesians chapter 2 because we need to clearly understand what I mean by the world coming against us as Christians and trying to get us to turn away from God.

01:53.012 --> 01:53.973
What is the world?

01:54.514 --> 01:55.495
Who is the world?

01:56.096 --> 01:58.098
We all know that we live in the world

01:58.786 --> 02:02.311
But what does the Bible mean by the world coming against the Christian?

02:02.911 --> 02:19.454
If you look in Ephesians chapter 2, it says, and you were dead and your trespasses and sins in which you formerly walked according to the course of this world, according to the prince of the power of the heir of the spirit that is now working in the sons of disobedience.

02:20.355 --> 02:25.842
Among them we too all formerly lived in the lust of the flesh and the lust of our flesh,

02:25.954 --> 02:33.345
indulging the desires of the flesh and of the mind and whereby nature, children of wrath, even as the rest.

02:34.967 --> 02:53.074
The world in the Bible refers to every thought, every message, every philosophy, every deed, every action that is contrary to the will of God, that is contrary to the character of God.

02:53.698 --> 02:58.864
there is a sense in which we were of the world before we became Christians.

02:59.885 --> 03:09.936
And the people in this world who have yet to receive Christ as Lord and Savior are still in the world and they function according to the world.

03:10.736 --> 03:23.250
And they even come against the believer knowingly or unknowingly and oftentimes cause them great damage by leading them into sin or leading them away from Christ.

03:23.522 --> 03:26.867
So I want you to look, let's just look at this definition.

03:27.548 --> 03:30.032
You were dead and your trespasses and sins.

03:31.034 --> 03:48.982
All of us were born spiritually dead, unresponsive to the righteousness of God, unresponsive to the voice of God, but very responsive to this fallen world, to our own fallen flesh, to sin and even to the devil.

03:50.564 --> 03:51.826
It says in verse two,

03:52.162 --> 03:59.074
in which you formally walked according to the course of this world, according to the prince of the power of the air.

04:00.797 --> 04:09.352
Outside of Christianity, outside of faith in Christ, outside of the true church, people live a certain way.

04:10.093 --> 04:14.661
And the way that they live is almost atheistic or agnostic.

04:14.701 --> 04:17.426
They live as though God did not exist.

04:17.826 --> 04:20.949
Or if he does exist, he's not made himself known.

04:21.209 --> 04:22.951
He's not made his commandments known.

04:23.551 --> 04:23.912
Okay.

04:24.332 --> 04:40.067
And so people live in a way that is contrary to the nature and will of God, but not only that, it says they live according to the prince of the power of the air of the spirit that is now working in the sons of disobedience.

04:40.768 --> 04:42.469
This is a reference to the devil.

04:43.390 --> 04:47.314
And so people are not only living in ignorance,

04:47.938 --> 04:50.541
with regard to God, His nature and His will.

04:51.502 --> 05:06.621
They're not only dead to God and unresponsive, but they're alive, not only to the lust of their flesh, but actually to the devil and the demonic, the spirits, the fallen spirits of this age.

05:07.442 --> 05:11.967
They're responsive to them, and they're also activated by them.

05:12.888 --> 05:17.554
So when a person sins, we know it is their fault, it is their doing.

05:17.730 --> 05:26.459
but also behind it could be not only the temptation, but also the animation, power of the devil.

05:27.580 --> 05:34.967
And because of this, everyone outside of Christ is referred to as a son of disobedience.

05:35.467 --> 05:46.258
They belong to God in that he created them, but their lives are marked, not by obedience to the will of God, but by disobedience to the will of God.

05:46.658 --> 05:55.272
And then verse three, he reminds us, you know, we need to be careful not to be self-righteous or to judge people outside of Christ.

05:55.392 --> 05:55.692
Why?

05:56.113 --> 06:04.907
Because we were also formally outside of Christ before we heard the gospel, repented of our sins and believed.

06:05.548 --> 06:14.482
And we also followed the lust of our flesh, of our fallen flesh, and we indulged in the desires of the flesh and of the mind,

06:14.626 --> 06:16.729
and we're by nature children of wrath.

06:17.710 --> 06:26.741
Before someone becomes a Christian, it's not only that they do bad things, but their nature is fallen.

06:26.961 --> 06:33.569
Their nature is morally corrupt, and it is from that corruption that the fruit of their life comes forth.

06:33.629 --> 06:37.213
And we were a part of that, but now we are Christian.

06:37.474 --> 06:44.402
And as Christian, as believers in Christ, our nature has been changed, our desires have been changed,

06:44.866 --> 06:51.112
And because of that, our actions, our words, even our thoughts are changed.

06:51.252 --> 06:53.374
And so in the world, what do we have?

06:53.434 --> 07:07.288
We have two groups of people, those in Adam and outside of Christ and those who are in Christ, those who are in Christ seek to live a certain way according to the nature and will of God.

07:08.049 --> 07:13.554
But those who are outside of Christ who have yet to believe, they live

07:14.498 --> 07:18.163
they speak in a completely different way.

07:18.544 --> 07:26.275
And they're not content just to be here alone, but they also desire to influence the believer.

07:26.315 --> 07:33.465
You see, the believer is something of a thorn in their flesh.

07:34.146 --> 07:37.411
The believer is something like a pebble in their shoe.

07:38.453 --> 07:42.258
As the believer lives a righteous life, those in the world

07:42.466 --> 07:50.999
are convicted about their own sin and they desire for that believer to stop it, to become like them.

07:51.059 --> 07:59.873
And so what you need to understand young person is you live in a world where the majority of the people are not followers of Jesus Christ.

08:00.714 --> 08:10.930
They live a completely different way because they think a completely different way because they have a completely different nature and they're always going to seek to be

08:11.298 --> 08:12.339
and influence.

08:13.200 --> 08:19.367
And to be honest with you, they have the greater control over all the mediums of influence.

08:21.069 --> 08:40.850
They outpopulate us, number one, but also there is radio, television, internet, Instagram, social media, Twitter, the news, even the entertainment, it is all designed to draw the Christian away from Christ.

08:41.026 --> 08:42.348
And so we need to be careful.

08:42.988 --> 08:43.329
Okay.

08:43.729 --> 08:44.931
Now let's go back.

08:46.112 --> 08:48.935
Let's go back to Proverbs chapter six.

08:50.357 --> 08:56.764
And I want to reread verses 10 through 21.

08:58.406 --> 09:06.836
Remember this woman in our study is representing the world and the temptations of the world to get us to do unrighteousness.

09:07.477 --> 09:08.338
And verse 10.

09:08.962 --> 09:12.826
Behold, a woman comes to meet him dressed as a harlot and cunning of heart.

09:12.846 --> 09:14.588
She is boisterous and rebellious.

09:15.069 --> 09:16.651
Her feet do not remain at home.

09:17.131 --> 09:21.917
She is now in the streets, now in the squares, and lurks by every corner.

09:22.657 --> 09:24.660
So she seizes him and kisses him.

09:24.680 --> 09:29.685
And with a brazen face, she says to him, I was due to offer peace offerings.

09:30.106 --> 09:31.547
Today I've paid my vows.

09:31.647 --> 09:33.970
Therefore, I have come out to meet you.

09:34.242 --> 09:42.093
To seek your presence earnestly, and I have found you, and I have spread my couch with coverings, with colored linens of Egypt.

09:42.153 --> 09:45.197
I have sprinkled my bed with mirth, aloes, and cinnamon.

09:45.597 --> 09:48.061
Come let us drink our fill of love until morning.

09:48.461 --> 09:50.704
Let us delight ourselves with caresses.

09:51.165 --> 09:53.568
For my husband is not at home.

09:54.009 --> 09:55.591
He has gone on a long journey.

09:55.631 --> 09:57.954
He has taken a bag of money with him.

09:57.974 --> 10:00.818
At the full moon, he will come home.

10:01.186 --> 10:05.633
With her many persuasions, she entices him with her flattering lips.

10:06.193 --> 10:07.676
She seduces him.

10:08.276 --> 10:18.051
Now, from these verses, we can find several characteristics, discover many characteristics that are found in the world.

10:18.431 --> 10:22.417
This woman acts in the same way that the world does toward us.

10:23.198 --> 10:28.086
In verse 10, the world's outward appearance hides its inner reality.

10:28.626 --> 10:28.987
Okay?

10:29.327 --> 10:31.090
She's dressed up really nice.

10:31.490 --> 10:35.996
Maybe she looks very attractive, but she's actually very, very dangerous.

10:36.496 --> 10:44.106
And though the outside may appear beautiful inside, there's moral rot inside.

10:44.166 --> 10:45.808
She stinks inside.

10:46.549 --> 10:47.170
She's ugly.

10:47.791 --> 10:50.034
Also, she is cunning.

10:50.054 --> 10:51.896
She's cunning of heart.

10:52.617 --> 10:53.298
Young people

10:53.506 --> 10:58.311
Um, the world is very cunning, very wise in a shrewd and evil way.

10:58.351 --> 11:03.037
Now some of you young people, you think you're so smart.

11:03.097 --> 11:04.939
You think you know so much about the world.

11:04.959 --> 11:09.284
Do you think you know more than your parents about the world?

11:09.384 --> 11:10.926
I mean, how could they know they're old?

11:11.707 --> 11:12.948
Well, it's just the opposite.

11:13.849 --> 11:21.778
You're no match for the world and the world can take you and deceive you and change you and ruin you.

11:22.018 --> 11:27.005
And the reason why your parents are the way they are is because they realize something you don't.

11:27.526 --> 11:35.537
The world is an extraordinarily dangerous place that has ruined many young people like you.

11:36.298 --> 11:41.645
Also, the world hides its true intent.

11:42.166 --> 11:48.234
Again, remember, she looks wonderful on the outside, but on the inside, she's right.

11:48.715 --> 11:51.058
Also, she comes to the young man,

11:51.170 --> 11:55.597
just like the world will come to you as though she really, really cared about him.

11:56.799 --> 12:00.244
The world will come to you like it really, really cares about you.

12:00.805 --> 12:04.431
But in reality, all it wants to do is use you.

12:05.453 --> 12:08.478
Verse 11, she is boisterous and rebellious.

12:08.558 --> 12:10.060
Her feet do not remain at home.

12:10.100 --> 12:11.542
The world is boisterous.

12:12.304 --> 12:18.834
It's full of noise, full of conflict, full of, well, just

12:19.714 --> 12:23.418
People who have no peace.

12:24.379 --> 12:28.103
People who are always at odds with one another.

12:28.424 --> 12:35.231
The world is like a sea, the Bible says, churning and bringing up all the filth from the bottom.

12:35.812 --> 12:36.252
Do you see?

12:37.153 --> 12:39.916
Also, she's rebellious, verse 11.

12:40.597 --> 12:44.882
It says, her feet do not remain at home.

12:45.474 --> 12:46.575
Well, let's read the whole thing.

13:03.050 --> 13:15.442
When your parents come to you and they want to explain things to you, when they want to give you a command or a direction, how does your heart respond?

13:15.810 --> 13:18.054
Do you think to yourself, what a blessing.

13:18.294 --> 13:26.647
I have parents that care enough about me to give me guidelines and parameters to build fences of protection around me.

13:26.988 --> 13:28.551
Do you appreciate them for that?

13:28.991 --> 13:31.055
Or do you get angry?

13:31.635 --> 13:33.579
Is your heart like the heart of the world?

13:33.659 --> 13:35.422
Is your heart like the heart of this woman?

13:37.084 --> 13:43.154
Whenever anybody tells you something to do, you want to do just the opposite.

13:43.426 --> 13:46.751
Also in verse 11, it says, her feet do not remain at home.

13:47.212 --> 13:47.973
What does that mean?

13:48.333 --> 13:49.936
She's always discontent.

13:50.336 --> 13:51.878
She's never satisfied.

13:52.199 --> 13:55.564
She's always seeking for something new.

13:55.604 --> 14:03.896
One of the greatest evidences that you are becoming mature in Christ is that you're content.

14:04.677 --> 14:05.438
You're happy.

14:05.458 --> 14:07.161
You're satisfied.

14:07.561 --> 14:10.706
No matter what your circumstance is, why?

14:11.458 --> 14:14.102
because all your delight comes from him.

14:14.142 --> 14:18.948
And he's the same yesterday, today, and forever.

14:19.870 --> 14:25.838
In verse 12 and 13, she is now in the streets, now in the squares and lurks by every corner.

14:25.898 --> 14:27.741
So she seizes him and kisses him.

14:28.041 --> 14:32.948
And with a brazen face, she says to him, what does all this mean?

14:33.769 --> 14:35.151
The world is predatory.

14:36.313 --> 14:40.178
Notice that she is in the streets and she's hunting

14:40.258 --> 14:41.399
this young man.

14:42.180 --> 14:53.294
It's not that she's just going to go over in a corner somewhere and be all by herself and do evil all by herself, but what she wants is to draw other people into that evil.

14:53.955 --> 14:55.437
The world is the same way.

14:56.318 --> 15:03.668
It's not content just to be over here doing what it wants to do and leaving you alone to follow Christ and follow righteousness.

15:03.968 --> 15:05.650
That's not what's going to happen.

15:05.730 --> 15:07.454
The world is predatory.

15:07.835 --> 15:14.593
When it sees someone like you wanting to follow Christ, it wants to stop you, change you, turn you.

15:15.655 --> 15:19.485
And if you won't turn, if you won't join them, ruin you.

15:20.307 --> 15:20.628
Okay?

15:21.350 --> 15:22.994
Also, look at verse 14.

15:23.490 --> 15:25.773
I was due to offer peace offerings today.

15:25.833 --> 15:27.255
I've paid my vows here.

15:27.275 --> 15:36.168
This lady is wanting this young man to do something that is against the will of God while at the same time she claims to be religious.

15:37.289 --> 15:39.492
The world is religious.

15:41.114 --> 15:52.370
And there are many, many people who boast of being quite religious or even super spiritual, but the true test of whether or not your religion is correct.

15:52.994 --> 16:03.384
is biblical is really a part of you is that you will know and submit to the will of God as it is revealed in the Scriptures.

16:03.724 --> 16:09.890
Look at verse 15, therefore I've come out to meet you to seek your presence earnestly and I have found you.

16:09.930 --> 16:11.091
What else does the world do?

16:11.131 --> 16:13.634
It flatters you.

16:13.874 --> 16:16.436
It makes you feel special.

16:16.977 --> 16:17.677
I've come out.

16:18.878 --> 16:20.680
I've been looking for you everywhere.

16:21.041 --> 16:22.642
You're so important to me.

16:24.546 --> 16:34.958
But that person who speaks that way, when the world comes to you that way, it's like a spider coming to a fly or a cougar to a deer or a hunter to an elk.

16:36.801 --> 16:37.742
They're seeking you.

16:38.643 --> 16:44.670
You're important to them, but just so that they can use you, devour you and ruin you.

16:45.091 --> 16:51.378
Also 16 and 18, I've spread my couch with coverings, my colored linens of Egypt.

16:52.322 --> 16:53.243
What does this mean?

16:53.263 --> 16:58.570
Also for 17, I've sprinkled my bed with mirth and aloes and cinnamon.

16:59.150 --> 17:00.672
The world beautifies sin.

17:01.654 --> 17:11.466
She's decorated her room in order to bring that young man into her room and do things that are contrary to the will of God.

17:12.847 --> 17:14.389
Here's one of the things you've got to see.

17:14.429 --> 17:21.458
Sin will always appear, not only spiritual or religious, proper,

17:22.050 --> 17:32.026
But it will present itself as something that is beautiful, something that is attractive, at least until it's too late.

17:33.909 --> 17:39.237
You have to understand that the world's propaganda is absolutely marvelous.

17:40.780 --> 17:44.626
But the reality is something quite different.

17:45.186 --> 17:46.507
Let me give you an idea.

17:46.527 --> 18:05.889
I was telling a young man one time we were going down the road and there was this huge billboard of, I think, a beautiful woman and she was drinking and drinking with other people and they seemed to be rather, you know, quite involved with drinking and partying and other things.

18:06.469 --> 18:08.552
And I told that young man, I said, look at that.

18:10.294 --> 18:14.258
That's a kind of a pretty and attractive picture, isn't it?

18:14.946 --> 18:19.173
The problem is they don't show you the other side of the story.

18:19.513 --> 18:26.944
If we could go behind the billboard and look, we would see all those people quite sick, quite ruined and at a loss.

18:28.247 --> 18:28.547
Okay.

18:29.208 --> 18:31.111
So the world beautifies sin.

18:31.512 --> 18:36.339
Now we get to verse 19 and 20, for my husband is not at home.

18:36.439 --> 18:38.322
He has gone on a long journey.

18:38.882 --> 18:42.286
He has taken a bag of money with him at the full moon.

18:42.606 --> 18:43.768
He will come home.

18:44.168 --> 18:45.290
Now, what's going on here?

18:45.830 --> 18:47.773
Well, we're going to get to it in the next lesson.

18:48.594 --> 18:53.740
But what is really going on here is she saying, Hey, we can do this.

18:54.821 --> 18:57.324
We can get ourselves involved in sin.

18:57.464 --> 19:02.310
We can be contrary to the will of God, even contrary to the will of her husband.

19:03.011 --> 19:04.493
And we won't get caught.

19:05.334 --> 19:07.416
No one will see us.

19:07.977 --> 19:08.818
My husband.

19:09.218 --> 19:10.700
Who should be watching over me?

19:10.740 --> 19:11.942
He's gone.

19:12.683 --> 19:18.392
And so we can do anything we want and there will be no negative consequences.

19:19.494 --> 19:22.338
We're going to see that that's just not true.

19:22.899 --> 19:26.885
There are always consequences to sin.

19:26.945 --> 19:36.159
And even though you escape the notice of everyone, you will never escape the notice of God.

19:37.301 --> 19:37.842
Let's pray.

19:40.322 --> 20:08.146
Father, I pray that you would use this as the warning in the life of so many young people that they would come to understand that this world is a dangerous place, that it is filled with people who would like to do nothing more than divert a Christian from walking in the will of God.

20:09.890 --> 20:23.049
Please help them to see, Lord, help them to realize that it is truly a dangerous place and the only safe haven is in Christ and in obedience to His commands.

20:24.430 --> 20:38.290
O Father, I pray for every young person who's listening, that you would protect them from the evil within them, but also Father, I pray that you would protect them from evil men and women,

20:38.466 --> 20:41.435
and evil circumstances in this life.

20:42.979 --> 20:51.162
Oh God, I pray that you would raise up a generation of young people who love you and who walk in integrity.

20:51.764 --> 20:53.810
In Jesus name, amen.

